rComments: Honestly, she was such a kind professor who really cares about her work and her students. She helps in any way she can and makes the course enjoyable and not difficult. Loved her.

The course sounds really amazing from the description, the material might be interesting but the lectures don't do it justice. Prof. Baker basically reads off of her slides, which are not very helpful. The focus of the class was mainly on cuneiform writing. Only take this course if you are extremely interested in the Ancient Near East.
She is a fair-marker and the assignments are easy to do well in. The final exam was a bit difficult but it was all multiple choice.
